<FIRST>r a AM-HostageStalemate     03-19 0311</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Hostage Stalemate,0323</SECOND>
<HEAD>Armed Man Holds Family Hostage</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SPRINGFIELD, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An armed man who police say had been
hospitalized recently for depression was holding his girlfriend, her
sister and the girlfriend's 4-year-old daughter hostage late
Saturday.
   Heavily armed police remained in position around a one-story home
where Douglas ``Dougie'' Thomas, 20, was holding the three hostages.
   A fourth hostage, the 2{-month-old daughter of Thomas and his
girlfriend, was released in the morning, pushed out of the house
wrapped in a quilt, police said.
   Police blocked off streets leading to the house and evacuated
about 32 families about five hours after receiving the first reports
of the disturbance late Friday.
   Thomas was reportedly armed with a handgun and threatened to kill
himself and the hostages. Twice during the day he fired shots inside
the house, but he allowed the hostages to talk to police each time
to show they had not been harmed, police said.
   ``We're just going to wait,'' said Police Chief Mike Walton.
``Right now, everything is under control.''
   Police spokesman Neil Williamson said Thomas had made no specific
demands but he repeatedly asked to talk to friends and relatives by
telephone.
   ``He seems like he's almost hallucinating,'' said police
spokesman Neil Williamson. He said Thomas was hospitalized recently
for depression and apparently had been taking medication that might
affect his mood.
   James Kerr, a friend who talked to Thomas by telephone during the
afternoon, described him as ``paranoid and insecure.''
   Although Williamson refused to identify him, relatives, friends
and other police sources confirmed Thomas' identity, according to
the Springfield State Journal-Register.
   Thomas spent a year in prison for aggravated battery for shooting
two men at a dance in 1985, the newspaper reported.
   Police also did not identify the hostages. However, others said
they were Karen Lambert, 20, Thomas's girlfriend; Nikki Lambert, 14;
and Katrina Lambert, 4.
</TEXT>
