<FIRST>r i AM-France-Drownings     03-19 0138</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-France-Drownings,0140</SECOND>
<HEAD>Five Drown When Auto Falls Into Seine River</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MELUN, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A small car with 10 youths jammed inside
fell into the Seine River early Sunday in the town of St. Mammes,
and five of the passengers drowned, police said.
   The automobile, a four-seated Fiat, was being driven down a
riverside street at about 4 a.m. in the town 45 miles southeast of
Paris when it went into the river, police said. The 22-year-old
driver and four of the passengers were able to pull themselves out
of the water, but the others drowned.
   Three bodies were found trapped in the car, and divers found two
more in the river. Police said the victims lived nearby and ranged
in age from 14 to 17, but did not immediately identify them or the
driver by name.
</TEXT>
