<HEAD>Two Killed, 150 Hurt In Train Wreck In South Africa</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two passenger trains collided
head-on Sunday, killing two people and injuring at least 80, a
railroad spokeswoman said.
   The collision occurred at 2:30 p.m. at a commuter station on the
western outskirts of Johannesburg.
   The two trains were traveling in oppositie directions on a rail
line linking Johannesburg with Randfontein, a town 20 miles to the
west.
   The driver of one of the trains and a passenger were killed,
according to Yvette Marais, a spokeswoman for South African
Transport Services. She said from 80 to 100 passengers were injured.
   The cause of the crash was not known.
</TEXT>
