<FIRST>r i AM-Greenpeace-USShip     03-19 0178</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Greenpeace-US Ship,0182</SECOND>
<HEAD>Greenpeace Protests Visit Of American Cruiser</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CORK, Ireland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Protesters from the environmental group
Greenpeace chained themselves to a pier near Cork on Sunday in an
attempt to prevent the U.S. cruiser Yorktown from docking.
   Police in southern Ireland said about a dozen demonstrators were
involved in the protest and that after some scuffling with police
they were removed.
   The demonstrators continued their protest on the wharf, chanting
slogans and singing peace songs, as the guided missile cruiser
docked.
   Greenpeace said the Yorktown is a nuclear warship, but Robert
White, defense attache at the U.S. Embassy in Dublin, told RTE,
Ireland's national radio network, it was not carrying nuclear
weapons.
   A Greenpeace spokeswoman, Orla Ni Eili, said the Yorktown is
equipped with anti-submarine rockets capable of firing
nuclear-tipped warheads.
   ``The immediate dangers to Cork residents with the presence of
such a dangerous visitor are horrifying, and evacuation and
emergency plans for Cork would not be adequate to deal with an
accident,'' she said.
   The Yorktown arrived for a three-day courtesy visit to Cork.
</TEXT>
