<FIRST>r i AM-Switzerland-Riot     03-19 0134</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Switzerland-Riot,0137</SECOND>
<HEAD>Demonstrators Clash With Police in Downtown Zurich</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ZURICH, Switzerland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police using tear gas and rubber
bullets clashed with about 100 youths who threw bottles and rocks in
a protest against Zurich's chronic shortage of inexpensive housing.
   One police car was set ablaze by a gasoline bomb and some store
windows were broken in the riot Saturday night in downtown Zurich,
but no one was injured or arrested, police said Sunday.
   The protest began peacefully but turned violent when police
briefly detained a youth who was caught painting slogans on a wall.
   Police said the riot, the city's worst in recent years, caused
more than $125,000 in damage. It was the third time in a month that
demonstrations against the shortage of low-rent apartments in the
city have become violent.
</TEXT>
